balanceOf(address,uint256).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOf}. Requirements: - `account` cannot be the zero address.

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

batchMint(address,uint256[],uint256[],by.details: Mint tokens for each id in _ids

params._data: Data to pass if receiver is contract
params._quantities: Array of amounts of tokens to mint per id
params._to: The address to mint tokens to

create(address,uint256,string,bytes).details: Creates a new token type and assigns _initialSupply to an address NOTE: remove onlyOwner if you want third parties to create new tokens on your contract (which may change your IDs)

params._data: Data to pass if receiver is contract
params._initialOwner: address of the first owner of the token
params._initialSupply: amount to supply the first owner
params._uri: Optional URI for this token type

mint(address,uint256,uint256,bytes).details: Mints some amount of tokens to an address

params._data: Data to pass if receiver is contract
params._to: Address of the future owner of the token

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBaseMetadataURI(string).details: Will update the base URL of token's URI

params._newBaseMetadataURI: New base URL of token's URI

setCreator(address,uint256[]).details: Change the creator address for given tokens

params._ids: Array of Token IDs to change creator

setTokenURI(uint256,string).details: Will update the token URL of token's URI

totalSupply(uint256).details: Total amount of tokens in with a given id.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
